ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend it as a useful way to read some important primary sources.
This is a great class - a strong survey of vital and often underread texts with two superb professors.
I would recommend this class to a student who is interested in the intellectual and artistic development of this time period.
Yes, I would recommend the course, and would think even non-RNST students might take it...

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course acquainted me with a range of primary material I'd never read.
This class gave me some insight in the intellectual progression that leads into the time period that I am interested in studying.
This course has helped me get a sense of the wonder context on which Spenser and others wrote and it has introduced me to new texts...
